12
00:00:31,001 --> 00:00:35,000
This is a base that we use to
track and analyze user feedback.

13
00:00:35,001 --> 00:00:37,000
This base contains two tables.

14
00:00:37,001 --> 00:00:40,000
User feedback and feedback analysis.

15
00:00:40,001 --> 00:00:43,000
And each table contains views
that we're going to review later.

16
00:00:43,001 --> 00:00:46,000
As you can see it is very similar to a
spreadsheet but there are some extra

17
00:00:46,001 --> 00:00:48,000
fields like the attaching ones.

18
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:52,000
To add a new field, click on
the plus button and select one.

19
00:00:52,001 --> 00:00:57,484
We have many options here like AutoNumber,
Collaborator, Formula, Rating but

20
00:00:57,509 --> 00:00:59,898
two really important
fields are the link field

21
00:00:59,922 --> 00:01:02,385
that will let you connect
tables and the lookup

22
00:01:02,410 --> 00:01:04,225
field that will
allow you to bring

23
00:01:04,237 --> 00:01:07,000
information to a table
from another table.

24
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,743
Let's add a date field.

25
00:01:13,050 --> 00:01:14,736
Now we can select
dates on this field.

26
00:01:17,762 --> 00:01:20,000
You can also use the
Manage Fields button.

27
00:01:20,350 --> 00:01:24,000
In case your table has many fields
and you want to quickly make changes or

28
00:01:24,001 --> 00:01:25,130
add new fields.

29
00:01:25,556 --> 00:01:30,096
If you want to delete a record, just
click on this arrow and then on Delete.

30
00:01:31,382 --> 00:01:34,149
To add a record to this
table, we have several options.

31
00:01:34,476 --> 00:01:38,309
The first one is to click on an
empty cell and type the information in.

32
00:01:40,523 --> 00:01:44,000
The second way is to click
on the Add a Record button.

33
00:01:44,001 --> 00:01:46,000
Then just complete
the fields and that's it.

34
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:48,000
The record will be added.

35
00:01:48,001 --> 00:01:50,000
The last one is by using a form.

36
00:01:50,001 --> 00:01:53,679
This table already has a form but later
on I will show you how to create one.

37
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:56,896
Under Views, we can see Feedback Form.

38
00:01:57,243 --> 00:01:58,050
Let's open it.

39
00:01:59,503 --> 00:02:01,041
Here we can edit the form.

40
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:05,000
For example if we need to change
the name of the fields or hide fields.

41
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:06,989
But the cool part is
that you can click on

42
00:02:07,015 --> 00:02:10,270
Get Form URL and
then if you open the link,

43
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:13,836
it will bring you to the form that you
can use to add records to your table.

44
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:17,716
You can share these form with others
so they can add records without having

45
00:02:17,741 --> 00:02:19,000
to open the table.

46
