00:02:24,001 --> 00:02:26,754
So, if you're interested, check
out the link in the description.

49
00:02:26,787 --> 00:02:28,189
Ok. Let's close this.

50
00:02:29,219 --> 00:02:30,019
And this.

51
00:02:31,593 --> 00:02:35,263
Up here we can see that there is
another table called Feedback Analysis.

52
00:02:35,690 --> 00:02:39,000
This table is similar to the
other one but has more fields.

53
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:43,723
Like a drop down called Category
and a multi select called Tags.

54
00:02:43,783 --> 00:02:46,202
But it also has this
link field that links

55
00:02:46,227 --> 00:02:48,402
this table with the
user feedback table.

56
00:02:48,427 --> 00:02:50,941
And also lookup field
that is showing the

57
00:02:50,953 --> 00:02:53,000
feedback text from
the other table as well.

58
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:56,000
This table has different views.

59
00:02:56,001 --> 00:03:00,000
The deadlines view is a calendar
view that shows when the records do.

60
00:03:00,001 --> 00:03:02,000
The grey boxes are the records.

61
00:03:02,001 --> 00:03:05,017
You can click on any of them to
see more information about the record.

62
00:03:05,513 --> 00:03:09,312
Another view is called Actionable
Feedback which is very similar to the

63
00:03:09,337 --> 00:03:11,000
default view but it is filter.

64
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:15,000
It is only showing records where
the actionable field is checked.

65
00:03:16,100 --> 00:03:19,943
Finally, we have the Stacked by
Category view which is a kanban view.

66
00:03:20,356 --> 00:03:24,396
You can move a record from one column
to another one by dragging and dropping it.

67
00:03:24,682 --> 00:03:26,642
To create a new
view, click on this plus

68
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:29,137
button and then select the
view that you want to create.

69
00:03:29,303 --> 00:03:31,201
Here's where you
can set up a new form.

70
00:03:31,225 --> 00:03:34,436
Keep in mind that the views you
create here are for this table only.

71
00:03:34,709 --> 00:03:37,000
OK, let's select Gallery.

72
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,256
And the view has been created.

73
00:03:38,523 --> 00:03:40,183
On the side panel,
you can drag and drop

74
00:03:40,208 --> 00:03:41,884
more fields that will
show on the cards.

75
00:03:42,944 --> 00:03:46,743
To delete a view, click on the
three dots and then on delete.

76
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:52,450
If you want to add a new table
to your base, click on this button.

77
00:03:53,630 --> 00:03:57,024
Then select if you want to start
with an empty table or import a file.

78
00:03:57,684 --> 00:04:01,000
You can import spreadsheets and
CSV files that you already have from your

79
00:04:01,001 --> 00:04:03,000
computer or from the cloud.

80
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:05,000
Let's go back and create a blank table.

81
00:04:09,050 --> 00:04:12,162
Here you can start adding new
records and link them to the other tables.

82
00:04:12,536 --> 00:04:16,000
To delete a table, click on
this arrow and then on delete.

83
00:04:19,116 --> 00:04:22,000
On the right side, we
can see the log button.

84
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,263
This panel shows
all the changes made

85
00:04:24,288 --> 00:04:27,000
to this table in a
chronological order.

86
00:04:27,001 --> 00:04:29,000
The next button is the
Automations button.

87
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:33,417
It allows you to create basic automations
within the tables in this space.

88
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:36,669
For example, this one sends
email when a record is created.

89
00:04:37,489 --> 00:04:40,609
Other actions are to create a
record and to update a record.

90
00:04:40,883 --> 00:04:44,000
I think the list of possible
automations will increase over time.

91
00:04:44,001 --> 00:04:48,000
If you want to share this space, click
on the Share button and either share

92
00:04:48,001 --> 00:04:51,004
